/target

# Cargo.lock IS committed: mnema ships binaries + an MCP server, so releases, CI, `cargo audit`,
# and `cargo deny` should all resolve to identical, pinned dependency versions (a transitive bump
# can't silently enter a release). The zero-dependency `mnema-core` is unaffected either way.

# Mnema stores are encrypted, machine-specific data — never source. `*.store` covers the
# CLI/MCP default filename (`mnema.store`); `*.mnema` covers the documented extension.
*.mnema
*.store

# Per-store key: the random secret that seals the sibling *.mnema. NEVER source.
*.key

# Per-store advisory lock file (mnema-mcp / mnema hold this to prevent concurrent writers).
*.lock
# ...but Cargo.lock is committed on purpose (see the top of this file); the `*.lock` glob above
# would otherwise swallow it.
!Cargo.lock

# This repo's own MCP store lives here (in-repo, never on C:). Encrypted + machine-specific.
.mnema/

# Project-scoped MCP config: machine-specific store path. Keep out of source control.
.mcp.json

# Benchmark-scan output — kept local, never published or committed.
.sota/

# The LoCoMo dataset for `benches/locomo.rs` — a third party's (~2.8 MB), downloaded on demand
# (see the bench header), never vendored into this repo.
locomo10.json
data/locomo10.json

# Internal design docs (ADRs, design proposal) — kept local, not published.
docs/

# Internal quality-gate tooling is machine-local and kept out of the repo entirely; its
# ignore rules live in .git/info/exclude rather than here.
